  "body": "Signed-off-by: travisn <tnielsen@redhat.com>\r\n\r\nDescription of your changes:\r\nPer the [security model](https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/design/security-model.md#proposed-changes) proposal:\r\n- There is one serviceAccount per namespace, one for `rook-system` and one for each cluster that is created: `rook-ceph-cluster`.  \r\n- The operator, agent, and discovery daemons all run with the `rook-system` service account\r\n- The OSD daemon runs with the `rook-ceph-cluster` service account. Other cluster daemons (mon, mgr, mds, rgw) run with the default service account since they do not require access to k8s resources.\r\n- Rook no longer creates service accounts, cluster roles, roles, etc. These must be created by the admin.\r\n\r\nDiffering from the security model spec, a ClusterRoleBinding was needed for several resources:\r\n- Rook CRDs: Watched and handled across all namespaces\r\n- Pods: The agent needs to analyze pods for fencing\r\n- PVs & PVCs: The operator provisioner needs to create, delete, list, etc\r\n- Nodes: Used to determine on which nodes to place mons\r\n- Storage classes: watched by the operator\r\n\r\nThe `rook-ceph-core` role was created for the namespace-specific resources and the `rook-ceph-global` role was created for cluster-wide resources.\r\n\r\nWhich issue is resolved by this Pull Request:\r\nResolves #1389\r\n\r\nChecklist:\r\n- [x] Documentation has been updated, if necessary.\r\n- [x] Pending release notes updated with breaking and/or notable changes, if necessary.\r\n- [ ] Test upgrade from v0.7.1",
